We developed a plugin and tested it on Jira 5.0.6, 5.2.9 and 6.1 to be sure it works (even on our other systems). It worked great and there were no issues using the plugin.
But when we rolled it out to the productive system it crashed the whole Jira. Even after the uninstallation of the plugin Jira was broken and we had to recreate it from a backup.

So it would be a great improvement, if you could make the Jira API more secure, so somithing like this cannot happen anymore.
